  <discussion>Pseudotsuga macrocarpa , a tree of scattered occurrence and of no concern for timber, is valuable for esthetics and watershed protection. The northernmost stands of the species, in Kern County, are about 35 kilometers east of the closest approach of P . menziesii .</discussion>
